'''香槟池'''（Champagne Pool）是[[新西兰|新西兰]][[北島_(新西兰)|北岛]][[怀卡托|怀卡托]]区怀奥塔普[[地热|地热]]区的一个著名景点。[[温泉|温泉]]位于[[罗托路亚|罗托路亚]]东南30公里，[[陶波|陶波]]50公里。香槟池的名称来自大量[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]的释出如同玻璃杯中[[香槟酒|香槟酒]]的气泡。温泉形成于900年前一次火山爆发的热液。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Lloyd, E. F.|year=1959|title=The hot springs and hydrothermal eruptions of Waiotapu|journal=New Zealand Journal of Geology and Geophysics|volume=2|issue=1|pages=141-176|url=http://books.google.com.hk/books?id=tiA4AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA141&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr#v=onepage&q&f=false|access-date=2013-02-02|archive-date=2014-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222152202/http://books.google.com.hk/books?id=tiA4AAAAIAAJ&pg=PA141&redir_esc=y&hl=zh-CN&sourceid=cndr#v=onepage&q&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>湖的直径约65米，最深处约为65米，估计容积为50,000立方米。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Hedenquist, J. W. |year=1986|title=Geothermal systems in the Taupo Volcanic Zone: Their characteristics and relation to volcanism and mineralisation|journal=Bulletin of the Royal Society of New Zealand |volume=23|pages=134-168}}</ref>

==水质化学==
香槟池地下深处的地热水温为260°C，<ref>{{cite journal|author=Giggenbach, W. F.; Sheppard, D. S.; Robinson, B. W.; Stewart, M. K.; Lyon, G. L.|year=1994|title=Geochemical structure and position of the Waiotapu geothermal field, New Zealand|journal=Geothermics |volume=23|issue=5-6|pages=599-644|doi= 10.1016/0375-6505(94)90022-1|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0375650594900221}}</ref>但是由于热量散发在空气中，池中水温保持在73°C到75°C。由于二氧化碳的释出，池水[[pH值|pH值]]相对恒定在5.5。释放的气体主要是二氧化碳，也含有少量[[氮气|氮气]]、[[甲烷|甲烷]]、[[氢气|氢气]]、[[硫化氢|硫化氢]]和[[氧气|氧气]]。<ref name="Jones">{{cite journal|author=Jones, B.; Renaut, R. W.; Rosen, M. R.|year=2001|title=Biogenicity of gold- and silver-bearing siliceous sinters forming in hot (75 C ) anaerobic spring-waters of Champagne Pool, Waiotapu, North Island, New Zealand|journal=Journal of the Geological Society|volume=158|issue=6|pages=895-911|doi=10.1144/0016-764900-131|url=http://mr.crossref.org/iPage/?doi=10.1144%2F0016-764900-131|access-date=2013-02-02|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304083605/http://mr.crossref.org/iPage/?doi=10.1144%2F0016-764900-131|dead-url=no}}</ref>硅酸地热液体中含有过饱和的[[类金属|类金属]]化合物，如[[硫化砷|硫化砷]]和[[硫化锑|硫化锑]]，其沉淀物呈现出橙色。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Pope, J. G.; Brown, K. L.; McConchie, D. M.|year=2005|title=Gold concentrations in springs at Waiotapu, New Zealand: Implications for precious metal deposition in geothermal systems|journal=Economic Geology|volume= 100|issue=4|pages=677-687|doi=10.2113/gsecongeo.100.4.677|url=}}</ref>色彩艳丽的沉淀物与香槟池周围灰白的[[二氧化硅|二氧化硅]]火山灰熔渣形成对比。 

==生物学==
尽管香槟池地球化学特性突出，但是关于它作为微生物形成的研究依然很少。氢气和二氧化碳或者氧气是[[產甲烷作用|产烷生物]]或氢氧化[[微生物|微生物]][[自养生物|自养]]生长的[[新陈代谢|新陈代谢]]能量来源。非培养生物方法提供了温泉中细丝状的、球菌状的和杆状的细胞形态的证据。<ref name="Jones"/><ref>{{cite journal|author=Mountain, B. W.; Benning, L. G.and Boerema, J. A.|year=2003|title=Experimental studies on New Zealand hot spring sinters: rates of growth and textural development|journal=Canadian Journal of Earth Sciences|volume= 40|issue=11|pages=1643-1667|doi=10.1139/e03-068|url=http://www.nrcresearchpress.com/doi/abs/10.1139/e03-068|bibcode=10.1139/e03-068}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=Phoenix, V. R.; Renaut, R. W.; Jones, B. and Ferris, F. G.|year=2005|title=Bacterial S-layer preservation and rare arsenic-antimony-sulphide bioimmobilization in siliceous sediments from Champagne Pool hot spring, Waiotapu, New Zealand|journal=Journal of the Geological Society|volume=162|issue=2|pages=323-331|doi=10.1139/e03-068|url=http://mr.crossref.org/iPage/?doi=10.1144%2F0016-764903-058|access-date=2013-02-02|archive-date=2014-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140222053338/http://mr.crossref.org/iPage/?doi=10.1144%2F0016-764903-058|dead-url=no}}</ref>两种特别的[[细菌|细菌]]和一种[[古菌|古菌]]被成功地从香槟池分离出来。<ref>{{cite journal|author=Hetzer, A.; Morgan, H. W.; McDonald, I. R. and Daughney, C. J.|year=2007|PMID=17426919|title=Microbial life in Champagne Pool, a geothermal spring in Waiotapu, New Zealand|journal=Extremophiles|volume=11|issue=4|pages=605-614|doi=10.1007/s00792-007-0073-2|url=http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs00792-007-0073-2|access-date=2013-02-02|archive-date=2014-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223042148/http://link.springer.com/article/10.1007%2Fs00792-007-0073-2|dead-url=no}}</ref>

